<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Sting2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Sting,</orth> vb. (impf. and partic. <emph>stung</emph>) to hurt with a point darted out; absol.: <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.329" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 329</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.73" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 73</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.2.89" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 2, 89</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.6.94" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 6, 94</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.56" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.1.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 1, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 5.1.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. V, 1, 38</bibl>. With an object: <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.69" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. IV, 1, 69</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.131" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 2, 131</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.3.58" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.240" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 240</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.1.16" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.229" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 229</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.229" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 229</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.127" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 127</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.132" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 132</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.5.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 5, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.5.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 5, 36</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.5.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 5, 36</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lr 5.1.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 1, 56</bibl>. Used of other things causing a similar pain: <cit><quote>--ing nettles,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.18" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 2, 18</bibl></cit>. Figuratively, == to pain acutely: <cit><quote>envy did s. his high-pitched thoughts,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 40" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 40</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>there's something in't that --s his nature,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 4.3.4" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 3, 4</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>these things s. his mind so venomously,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 4.3.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 3, 47</bibl></cit>. cf. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.5.88" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 5, 88</bibl>.

